history.text: Hello
Let's talk!
Hello! How are you?  The movie is called Frozen. Have you seen it?
Actually No I haven't seen that movie
It is a 3D computer animated musical disney film - you should see it. It's really good!
That does sound interesting. Is it a Pixar film?
It is produced by Walt Disney Animation Studios, it is their 53rd featured film. Did you know it is inspired from a Hans Christian Anderson fairy tail?
Oh, right... Which fairy tale is that?
The fairy tale is called "The Snow Queen" - a story about a brave princess who sets out with a group of friends to finder her estranged sister.
That does sound like a good one. Do you know which actors provided voices for the characters?
Yes - Kristen Bell voiced Anna, Idina Menzel voiced Elsa, and Jonathan Groff was Kristoff. It is a starry cast for sure! Do you like these actors?
I like Kristen Bell. She's quite funny and I find her very attractive. She could be the princess in my dreams.
I don't think I know Idina Menzel
haha thats funny! The film has amazing reviews, especially for the music. It has a Rotten Tomatoes 89%, Metacritics 74/100, CinemaScore A+... and thats probably due to Idina Menzel's voice!
I guess the soundtrack is quite popular
It is! one critic said they could envision it as a Broadway musical. Another said it has Broadway-style songs. I would not be surprised if there is a version on Broadway already.
Have you ever seen a Broadway musical?
I think I have heard the title song... did it win any academy awards?

I have not unfortunately, but I would love to see Frozen if it is on Broadway. The story is very complex - comedy, adventure and animation all rolled into a musical. I'm not sure if it won any awards!
Who was your favorite character in the movie?

My favorite character is Anna, she is an adventurer and is dedicated to finding her sister Elsa (who is basically a magical ice princess
). She has to find her so that she can release the kingdom from an eternal winter.
Is there a villain?

Yes! at first it appears Elsa is a villian, but I dont think she is. I think she is just misunderstood and insecure. The real villian is Hans, who Anna falls in love with. Elsa ends up saving Anna from Hans by unleashing her powers
Why he is a bad guy?

I think Elsa knows things about him, I haven't watched the film in a while :) Offhand, I do know Hans's father the Duke of Weselton is angry about her ruining the engagement and banishes her. So Elsa turned the kingdom into an eternal winter
She sounds very crazy
she is, but so is anna! she is friends with an iceman named Kristoff and his reindeer Sven lol
Which do you think would be the better princess to marry? Elsa or Anna?
hmmm probably Anna, Elsa seems unstable due to her magical powers haha
But magical powers sounds sexy
I wonder what other powers she has
yeah but she turns everything she touches to ice - thats scary :)
and she has no control over it!
haha that is scary
I guess that means no sex
